Package: kodi-session-aptosid
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: flatpak, sddm, plasma-workspace
Replaces: aptosid-settings-kodi-flatpak (<< 20260702.1~)
Breaks: aptosid-settings-kodi-flatpak (<< 20260702.1~)
Architecture: all
Description: provide desktop session for Kodi
 Provides a desktop session for launching Kodi via flatpak in standalone GBM
 window management mode via a desktop display manager.
 .
 Also provides a "Kodi/Plasma Appliance" session that boots into Kodi and,
 on exit, alternates with a Plasma (Wayland) session and back again.

Package: cage-kiosk-aptosid
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 cage,
 uwsm
Architecture: all
Description: cage kiosk session launcher for aptosid
 Ships /usr/libexec/cage-kiosk, the client wrapper that cage-based kiosk
 sessions run inside cage: it calls "uwsm finalize" to publish the Wayland
 session environment to the systemd user manager and D-Bus -- so
 graphical-session.target and the xdg-desktop-portal services activate
 (pipewire and friends) -- and then execs the kiosk application.
 .
 Shared by the per-application cage kiosk session packages.

Package: browser-kiosk-aptosid
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 cage-kiosk-aptosid,
 firefox-esr | firefox | chromium
Architecture: all
Description: web browser (cage) Wayland session for aptosid
 A full-screen Wayland session that runs the default web browser
 (x-www-browser) in the cage compositor, launched through uwsm so it runs as a
 proper systemd/XDG session (environment.d, graphical-session.target and the
 socket-activated pipewire and xdg-desktop-portal services).
 .
 The browser keeps its normal interface (not --kiosk), so the user can manage
 it. Pick the browser by installing firefox-esr, firefox or chromium; the
 session follows the x-www-browser alternative.

Package: waydroid-kiosk-aptosid
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 cage-kiosk-aptosid,
 waydroid
Architecture: all
Description: Waydroid kiosk (cage) Wayland session for aptosid
 A full-screen "appliance" Wayland session that runs Waydroid (Android in a
 container) inside the cage kiosk compositor, launched through uwsm so it runs
 as a proper systemd/XDG session.
 .
 Waydroid additionally needs a one-time "waydroid init" and the binder kernel
 modules present at runtime.

